Text: You have a healthy new baby.
We'll take her to the nursery.
Wait, was this the right bed?
Yes, this was the moment \Nthe fateful mistake happened.
Was it your turn today, Nagi?
Oh, I'm taking the one with the big yolk.
The lecithin in egg yolk is good for memory.
Here we go again with the loner talk.
I bet that's why you can't make any friends.
What do you think, Sachi? \NLooking snazzy, aren't I?
What, are you in your rebellious phase now?
This family doesn't know how to calm down.
You shoved it in there when you \Nwere drunk yesterday, remember?
Get ready as quick as you can.
Her parents are looking \Nforward to meeting you, too.
As if they aren't eager to \Nmeet their real kid, too.
I never thought kids getting put in the \Nwrong bed at birth was a real thing.
Nagi, we'll see you at the dining hall.
Hey, are you joining their family?
I grew up here for sixteen years.
Do you really think I could \Naccept new parents now?
I'm leaving early to study at the library.
I have to beat my rival.
I can't believe you're actually \Nsomeone else's kid, though.
You're nothing like the rest of us.
Plus you're book smart, and a loner.
All those jokes about them finding\Nme at the river weren't that far off.
I don't want you to go away.
I'm going to tell them straight up
that I have no intention \Nof becoming their child.
They said they would honor my wishes.
Gotta get this over with quick \Nand get back to studying.
No! You need to think it through!
You were just pretending to kill yourself?
I was going to make a video \Nand upload it to Inusta.
But you had to go and get in my way.
You're going to start some drama.
That was all to get more followers?
What, is this girl famous or something?
I feel like I've seen her before.
I want to start some drama
so I can convince her that \NI'm not going to get married.
You can get married at sixteen.
Wow, people my age are already \Ngetting married, huh?
You're in the same kind \Nof situation I am, then?
You're a mix-up baby, \Nand I have an arranged engagement.
We both have family issues, I guess.
By the way, are you my age, then?
I'm a second-year at Orpheus Girls' Academy.
Think I could meet her \Nif I went to Orpheus?
This dumb crap is all they \Ntalk about during breaks.
She can't be this cute. \NI bet she's using filters.
Hang on, isn't Megurogawa \Na super-elite prep school?
You must be really smart, Nagi-kun!
That's it! I can use that!
Guess what? You're going to be my boyfriend.
A-Are you crazy? Why would I be?
Who would go out with a bratty \Nminefield of a woman like you?
You're so silly. I meant pretend.
Who has arranged marriages \Nthese days, anyway?
Why would I ever marry a guy when I don't \Nknow what he looks like or anything?
I don't know anything about \Nthe rich people's world.
"I have a boyfriend that \NI'm deeply in love with."
"He's really smart and \Nhe has a bright future."
"Oh, Erika, you could have told us sooner."
And that's how the marriage was called off.
And she lived happily ever after.
I see. You have quite the imagination.
But alas, in reality, it fails.
For I have no intention of cooperating.
I'm about to go see my real parents.
I don't have time for your games.
My future is on the line here!
If you don't want to get married, then don't.
I'm asking you because \NI don't have that option!
I can see that! You don't need to zoom in!
I don't think you can explain this away.
I'll just attach this clip of the video \Nto Megurogawa Academy's contact form.
The school's going to contact my parents!
They'll be concerned about \Nmy emotional well-being
who are going to feel responsible \Nand force me into their care!
Fine, as long as I can get \Nto where I'm going on time.
So, what do I have to do to \Npretend to be your boyfriend?
I've spent my entire life studying.
You're on Google right now, too!
Do it... Do it? Do it?!
Why don't you just use that?
Can't you just show them that picture?
It would prove that I have a boyfriend.
It must be nice being smart, huh?
You don't even need the Internet.
More like you're not even thinking.
This picture makes it look like there was an \Nincident, though, so let's take another one.
And above all, I'm not cute in it.
Is this girl really a rich \Nperson's daughter, though?
You just look like an idiot.
I'll send that video to your school.
And why does it look like I picked up
a random person off the street \Nto take a picture with?
Because I'm a random person off the street.
Quit griping and come with me!
We totally look like a real couple.
I just remembered a girl in my class who \Nwent for matching outfits with her boyfriend.
We look really close, don't we?
Not really. It just looks like we happened \Nto be wearing the same clothes.
Or like I've just been in an accident.
At least you don't look like \Na random stranger, right?
I'd like to buy all of this.
I'll buy it in one payment on my card.
Keep the outfit. Think of \Nit as an official uniform.
Th-The stuff about her \Nbeing a princess was true.
What kind of home does she come from?
Look happy, like you're \Nhaving a lit-ass time.
You have to act stronger if \Nyou're going to be my boyfriend.
That's better than the last one.
We aren't going to get anything better.
I'm going to go borrow the changing room.
She's only showing her parents. \NDo I really need to look strong?
Hang on... Is your family a yak—
So why did you want us to dress up like that?
I figured my parents wouldn't \Nbutt in if you looked strong.
I think a good photo is one that gives \Nyou the vibe of the moment.
but also the vibe, as in the feelings of \Nthe people in the photos and taking them.
That's why I try not to \Nedit my photos too much.
So I think I'll use this photo.
But that's the first one we took.
It's the one that makes us \Nlook the closest, though.
And it's kind of funny, right?
I guess... if you're happy with it.
I thought Amano-san and I lived \Nin totally different worlds.
I guess there's no point in trying \Nto deceive your parents.
What else am I supposed to do, then?
There's got to be something, right? Like...
I thought you didn't have \Na boyfriend, Erika-tan!
No way... Why are those guys here?
These guys are from the \Nhigh school next to mine.
I got doxxed a little while ago, \Nand now I'm dealing with stalkers.
Oh. I guess that's what \Nit's like being famous, huh?
You're a princess at a chaste \Nall-girls school, aren't you?
That's why we followed you, you know!
Why would you tell them the truth like that?
This is the problem with \Nstuck-up studying addicts.
You can't engage with these kinds of people.
Who do you think you are, asshole?!
Wait, are they picking \Na fight with me right now?
Those types of people need \Nto learn the painful way.
Umino Family wisdom: \N"If anyone picks a fight with you, win."
I just realized I have to punch him!
I'm going to ruin the mood!
They'll stop talking about me marrying \Nhim if I completely wreck the mood.
I guess that's better than trying \Nto get yourself canceled.
I've never seen a fight in person.
I promise I'll give him a good \Nwallop like you did, Nagi-kun.
If that's what you're gonna do, \Nyou might as well go whole hog.
Ma'am, it's time for you to come home.
Gah! They were tracking my GPS location!
I guess since I'll probably never \Nsee you again, I'll tell you...
I don't have any friends, \Nbecause of how I am.
But it kinda felt like we were \Non a date today. It was fun.
Too bad you're not the one \NI'm supposed to marry, Nagi-kun.
Nice to meet you. \NYou must be Nagi-kun.
We thought you weren't \Ngoing to show up for us.
So anyway, Nagi, there's something \NI've been keeping from you.
The four of us parents talked it through.
we all care about our biological children, \Nas well as the children we raised.
It's been sixteen years, after all.
If the two of you got married, \Nyou'd both be our kids.
I was so surprised when I saw \Nthe photo my daughter sent me.
To think you two were \Nalready in a relationship!
It sure does speed things along.
To my daughter, Erika, with whom \Nyou were mixed up at birth.
I'm looking forward to your marriage.
But I have to keep my word.
There's been a change in circumstances!
I would have just let it slide before.
But now that I have a fiancée, \NI need to hurry.
I'm taking you down in the next exam!
The guy who's ranked second in our class!
I decided a long time ago...
What kind of person do I like?
That once I reached number one, \NI would confess to her.
And so, fate was set in motion.
I guess Nagi wasn't my actual brother.
This is an epic tale of love.
